{
  "stem": "11552.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was a mother with two children, a boy and a girl.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had strange feelings when I saw them, because I was angry at them that they have left such tracks that they were tracked down.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was angry at them because we are all going to die very soon, because I didn't know when they will come to pick them up, but I had tremendous compassion for them.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then I was mad at the Germans, why they should, you know, try to-- to take them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I was mad at the Ukrainians that they have told the Germans.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a whole anger and hatred towards the whole situation, but I [? gotted ?] them away from there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I brought them-- and it was daylight, mind you-- I had no choice-- I hid them, and then in the evening, I brought them to Wojciu's house.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I felt very badly about it, because I was kind of throwing these people without his permission.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Felt very badly.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You see, Kathy, with all that was happening, we children retained our sense of dignity.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We knew we couldn't do things like that, impose on somebody.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We had to have permission.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I knew I didn't have permission from Wojciu to bring these people-- I brought them anyway.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, he didn't like it at all.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was very indignant, but I let my mother handle him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was a coward, and I just left for a couple of days, because I was just really afraid that he's going to be angry-- very angry.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he accepted them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother-- my mother's hair got quite gray.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Her eyes were extremely sad, extremely sad.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But she lived for me.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
